        \eganswer
        Since the force isn't constant, it would be incorrect to 
        do $F = \Delta K/\Delta x$.
        Integrating both sides of the equation $\der{} K= F\der{} x$, we have
        \begin{align*}
                \Delta K        &= \int_{ x_{1}}^{ x_{2}} F\der{} x \\
